get.summary: Fish Health data export
get.description:
Endpoints to download export data for localities with salmonoid license as excel or csv files.
            
Cleaner fish data is not included after week 16, 2018, because of changes in reporting requirements.

parameters.name: reporttype
parameters.description:
'disease' gives suspected and confirmed ISA and PD cases. 'lice' gives reported lice
             counts pr week. 'treatments' gives reported medicinal treatments, cleanerfish deployed and mechanical
             removal.

parameters.name: filetype
parameters.description: Specifies output file format. 'xlsx', 'csv'

parameters.name: localityno
parameters.description: aquaculture site number

parameters.name: fromweek
parameters.description:
fromyear and fromweek specifies the first week to include in the export. Must
             correspond to a real year/week combination. If omitted, the export will include all weeks up to the
             specified toyear/toweek.

parameters.name: toweek
parameters.description:
toyear and toweek specifies the last week to include in the export. Must correspond
             to a real year/week combination. If omitted, the export will include data from the specified
             fromyear/fromweek (see above). If neither from or to is specified, the export will include all weeks.

with salmonoid license.

parameters.name: localityno

parameters.name: toweek
parameters.description:

            a real year/week combination. If omitted, the export will include data from the specified fromyear/fromweek
            (see above). If neither from or to is specified, the export will include all weeks.

get.summary: Detailed site information for a week
get.description:
Get full site information for a particular site and week specified by site id (localityNo), year and week.
In order to interpret this data correctly, familiarity with the lice reporting information from
the Norwegian Food Safety Authority (www.mattilsynet.no), ILA/PD disease information from
the Norwegian Veterinary Institute (www.vetinst.no) and aquaculture licenses from
the Norwegian Directorate of Fisheries (www.fiskeridir.no) is required.
            
Cleaner fish is not included after week 16, 2018, because of changes in reporting requirements.
            
The localityWeek information is updated nightly, with data reported to the Norwegian Food Safety Authority
via AltInn.

parameters.name: localityNo
parameters.description: site id

parameters.name: year
parameters.description: year part of ISO week date

parameters.name: week
parameters.description: week part of ISO week date

get.summary: Searchable list of fish slaughterhouses
get.description:
Get a list of all fish slaughterhouses. Only fish slaughterhouses with a geometry and with a valid
license at or after week 2019/23 are included.
            
The query can be used to filter the list. Establishment, Company and ApprovalNumber fields are used when
filtering.

parameters.name: query
parameters.description: search query

get.summary: Fish slaughterhouses by week
get.description: List of fish slaughterhouses for a specific week. No results for weeks before 2019/23.

get.summary: Fish slaughterhouse details
get.description: Details about a fish slaughterhouse for a specific week. No results for weeks before 2019/23.

204.description: Fish slaughterhouse not found, or har no valid license this week.

get.summary: Update status
get.description:
Get a timestamp for when the data sources was last imported. All other endpoint serve data last updated
at these times.

get.summary: Vessel track by week and a list of visited fish farms, disease zones.
get.description:
All vessel tracks for wellboats or other vessels for a complete week and all visited fish farms.
From week 35, 2020 all vessels that have visited a fish farm are included that week,
as well as all wellboats.
From week 35, 2020 the disease zones that the vessels pass through are also included.

parameters.name: mmsi
parameters.description: Maritime Mobile Service Identity - Identification number for a vessel

200.description: Vessel track by week and a list of visited fish farms, disease zones.

204.description: No vessel track data found for the given mmsi and week
